<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1234,2116,700,1324]" pageId="0" pageNumber="52">• Very small to medium-large insectivores; typically with short velvety fur, short tails, and spade-like, outwardly turned front feet; and predominantly fossorial, but also semi-fossorial, ambulatory, or semi-aquatic habits.</paragraph>
